Yeah.

00:41:48.300 --> 00:41:51.110
AUDIENCE: I have a question
about popular zombie movies

00:41:51.110 --> 00:41:54.400
and TV shows, where you see
them as truly scientifically

00:41:54.400 --> 00:41:58.670
inaccurate, either in general
or in specific important scenes.

00:41:58.670 --> 00:42:00.270
TIM VERSTYNEN:
Actually, I would say

00:42:00.270 --> 00:42:04.860
99% of the zombies
seen in TVs and movies

00:42:04.860 --> 00:42:09.240
are so unrealistic as
to make them impossible.

00:42:09.240 --> 00:42:12.560
There are a few exceptions.

00:42:12.560 --> 00:42:15.120
There is a video game,
"The Last of Us,"

00:42:15.120 --> 00:42:18.810
in which a evolution of
the cordyceps fungus, which

00:42:18.810 --> 00:42:23.470
actually induces zombieism
in ants-- really, it does--

00:42:23.470 --> 00:42:26.416
somehow mutates and causes the
same thing to happen in humans,

00:42:26.416 --> 00:42:28.040
so you see these
zombies running around

00:42:28.040 --> 00:42:30.350
with giant fungi
attached to their heads.

00:42:30.350 --> 00:42:33.287
And that is one that
I thought was actually

00:42:33.287 --> 00:42:35.620
a fairly realistic one, because
they're also not undead.

00:42:35.620 --> 00:42:38.140
You could easily kill them.

00:42:38.140 --> 00:42:40.740
And then the most
realistic representation

00:42:40.740 --> 00:42:45.480
of zombies that I would say
had the biological plausibility

00:42:45.480 --> 00:42:48.200
were the zombies in the "28
Days Later" and "28 Weeks Later"

00:42:48.200 --> 00:42:49.092
movies.

00:42:49.092 --> 00:42:50.800
And for those of you
who haven't seen it,

00:42:50.800 --> 00:42:53.989
the premise of the movie is
that scientists in Oxford

00:42:53.989 --> 00:42:56.530
are trying to understand rage,
and they develop a virus known

00:42:56.530 --> 00:43:00.094
as the rage virus, which
plays with the aggression

00:43:00.094 --> 00:43:01.010
circuits in the brain.

00:43:01.010 --> 00:43:04.080
And it gets loose in the
general public, and what happens

00:43:04.080 --> 00:43:08.850
is people just become really
just ravenously aggressive.

00:43:08.850 --> 00:43:10.050
They're not undead.

00:43:10.050 --> 00:43:12.699
In fact, the premise is that 28
days later means that they're

00:43:12.699 --> 00:43:14.240
not thinking about
eating, so they're

00:43:14.240 --> 00:43:16.120
going to starve to
death in 28 days.

00:43:16.120 --> 00:43:19.810
And so you can ideally wait
out the zombie apocalypse

00:43:19.810 --> 00:43:21.790
just by letting them
starve to death.

00:43:21.790 --> 00:43:23.540
So I thought that
probably "28 Days Later"

00:43:23.540 --> 00:43:25.440
was the most biologically
plausible one.

00:43:25.440 --> 00:43:28.120
But even then the behavioral
patterns and the transmission

00:43:28.120 --> 00:43:31.560
rates were nowhere
near plausible.

00:43:31.560 --> 00:43:33.670
The scene that
frustrated me the most

00:43:33.670 --> 00:43:35.880
was the last-- at the
end of "The Walking Dead"

00:43:35.880 --> 00:43:37.770
first season, when
they were in the CDC

00:43:37.770 --> 00:43:40.410
and there was this biologically
plausible explanation

00:43:40.410 --> 00:43:42.030
of the neuroscience of zombies.

00:43:42.030 --> 00:43:45.650
Was so bad that it made me cry.

00:43:45.650 --> 00:43:46.400
Yeah.

00:43:46.400 --> 00:43:48.191
AUDIENCE: So speaking
of realistic zombies,

00:43:48.191 --> 00:43:53.830
there's this notion
of the voodoo zombies

00:43:53.830 --> 00:43:58.840
and being controlled by
drugs on mutations and stuff.

00:43:58.840 --> 00:44:03.667
I'm just curious how
that plays into--

00:44:03.667 --> 00:44:04.500
TIM VERSTYNEN: Yeah.

00:44:04.500 --> 00:44:07.180
So that's actually another
little side tangent of mine,

00:44:07.180 --> 00:44:11.630
because the zombieism that you
see in Haitian voodoo culture

00:44:11.630 --> 00:44:15.180
is quite interesting
in that it has

00:44:15.180 --> 00:44:18.390
a proposed neuropharmacological
explanation.

00:44:18.390 --> 00:44:21.070
So there's a classic
book by Wade Davis, who

00:44:21.070 --> 00:44:24.210
was an ethnobotanist,
who went down to Haiti

00:44:24.210 --> 00:44:27.610
and made two particular
pharmacological links

00:44:27.610 --> 00:44:28.970
to Haitian zombieism.

00:44:28.970 --> 00:44:32.290
One was tetrodotoxin,
which was the poison used

00:44:32.290 --> 00:44:33.720
to simulate death.

00:44:33.720 --> 00:44:36.700
And tetrodotoxin works by
blocking the sodium channels

00:44:36.700 --> 00:44:39.830
that allow neurons to fire in
the peripheral nervous system.

00:44:39.830 --> 00:44:42.350
So your muscles
become paralyzed.

00:44:42.350 --> 00:44:46.150
And it actually won't kill
you unless your diaphragm

00:44:46.150 --> 00:44:47.440
stops working.

00:44:47.440 --> 00:44:49.707
So basically it kills you
because the diaphragm muscle

00:44:49.707 --> 00:44:50.290
stops working.

00:44:50.290 --> 00:44:53.190
But if you get a low
enough dose, what'll happen

00:44:53.190 --> 00:44:56.470
is that your diaphragm will
keep moving so slowly that you

00:44:56.470 --> 00:44:57.650
can't really detect it.

00:44:57.650 --> 00:45:00.060
But in all intents and
purposes you look dead.

00:45:00.060 --> 00:45:01.310
So that's the simulated death.

00:45:01.310 --> 00:45:03.570
And then the control
aspects, he proposed

00:45:03.570 --> 00:45:11.620
that the bokors, who are kind of
the bad or evil voodoo priests,

00:45:11.620 --> 00:45:15.120
would dose the individual after
the tetrodotoxin had worn off--

00:45:15.120 --> 00:45:16.670
when they dug them
out of their grave

00:45:16.670 --> 00:45:21.010
that they were buried alive in--
would douse them with Datura,

00:45:21.010 --> 00:45:23.010
which has three
major psychoactive

00:45:23.010 --> 00:45:26.850
ingredients, hyoscopine,
scopalamine, and atropine,

00:45:26.850 --> 00:45:27.800
I think.

00:45:27.800 --> 00:45:31.100
Each one of those will
induce a psychotic state.

00:45:31.100 --> 00:45:33.580
And so the idea is that you
can make this person who is now

00:45:33.580 --> 00:45:37.314
convinced that he's dead--
because he saw himself dead,

00:45:37.314 --> 00:45:39.730
he was well aware of everything
that was happening to him,

00:45:39.730 --> 00:45:41.960
felt buried-- and
then he gets raised

00:45:41.960 --> 00:45:44.000
and then there's a
psychoactive chemical

00:45:44.000 --> 00:45:45.489
that keeps him compliant.

00:45:45.489 --> 00:45:46.780
That was the Wade Davis theory.

00:45:46.780 --> 00:45:48.738
It's controversial, hasn't
been replicated yet.

00:45:48.738 --> 00:45:51.570
And people are saying that
there's probably other aspects

00:45:51.570 --> 00:45:54.480
to it that link more to
psychological belief.

00:45:54.480 --> 00:45:56.180
But yeah, the
Haitian voodoo zombie

00:45:56.180 --> 00:45:59.020
kind of links to neurobiology,
quite interesting that way.

00:46:01.820 --> 00:46:03.370
Yeah.

00:46:03.370 --> 00:46:05.210
