00:54:05.280 --> 00:54:07.462
And so what this guy,
James Papez would do is,

00:54:07.462 --> 00:54:09.920
he was trying to find a link
between emotion and intention.

00:54:09.920 --> 00:54:12.964
How is it that we can't remember
what we did at the store

00:54:12.964 --> 00:54:14.380
yesterday, but
everybody remembers

00:54:14.380 --> 00:54:15.671
where they were at 9/11, right?

00:54:15.671 --> 00:54:19.280
How do we have these emotional
bondings of memories?

00:54:19.280 --> 00:54:21.940
And so he mapped out
this theoretical circuit,

00:54:21.940 --> 00:54:24.620
and then would map it out in
cats by injecting the rabies

00:54:24.620 --> 00:54:26.930
virus and watching the
virus propagate from one

00:54:26.930 --> 00:54:28.740
area to the next, look
for the connections.

00:54:28.740 --> 00:54:32.530
And he actually made cats
that had memory problems,

00:54:32.530 --> 00:54:34.620
they were hyperaggressive.

00:54:34.620 --> 00:54:36.590
So we do a tongue-in-cheek
thing saying

00:54:36.590 --> 00:54:40.030
that James Papez made
the first zombie cats.

00:54:40.030 --> 00:54:44.790
But the rabies virus is a very
specific type of infection,

00:54:44.790 --> 00:54:47.260
and it's very general.

00:54:47.260 --> 00:54:51.430
So what it does is, it kind
of attacks a particular cell,

00:54:51.430 --> 00:54:53.710
jumps across what's
under the synapse, which

00:54:53.710 --> 00:54:56.340
is the gap between
cells, and keeps

00:54:56.340 --> 00:54:57.830
propagating down
to the next cell.

00:54:57.830 --> 00:54:58.870
And it just wanders.

00:54:58.870 --> 00:55:01.290
It just kind of follows
from place to place.

00:55:01.290 --> 00:55:04.220
So if you get an infection in
one part of the brain, where

00:55:04.220 --> 00:55:06.490
it goes is determined by
who it's connected with.

00:55:06.490 --> 00:55:08.780
And it'll keep traveling
until it basically

00:55:08.780 --> 00:55:11.190
kills the organism.

00:55:11.190 --> 00:55:13.250
Now normally you
get some symptoms

00:55:13.250 --> 00:55:16.560
like cognitive disorders.

00:55:16.560 --> 00:55:20.200
You'll get delusions and
dementia with rabies infection.

00:55:20.200 --> 00:55:24.260
You get hydraphobia,
so individuals

00:55:24.260 --> 00:55:26.782
infected with rabies virus
will be afraid of water.

00:55:26.782 --> 00:55:27.490
They won't drink.

00:55:27.490 --> 00:55:29.250
They become dehydrated.

00:55:29.250 --> 00:55:33.960
And some of those are
explained by the virus

00:55:33.960 --> 00:55:36.480
doesn't survive well when
there's lots of brain swelling,

00:55:36.480 --> 00:55:39.350
so it automatically
dehydrates you

00:55:39.350 --> 00:55:41.820
to keep that brain
swelling down.

00:55:41.820 --> 00:55:43.560
Things like that
have been put forth

00:55:43.560 --> 00:55:45.750
as explanations for
those kind of behaviors.

00:55:45.750 --> 00:55:47.291
But I think a lot
of them just happen

00:55:47.291 --> 00:55:49.780
to be, people show those
when the virus has spread

00:55:49.780 --> 00:55:52.900
so far throughout the brain
as to basically wipe away

00:55:52.900 --> 00:55:54.470
most of the neocortex.

00:55:54.470 --> 00:55:57.730
And so it's nonspecific in the
sense of where it's attacking,

00:55:57.730 --> 00:55:59.980
but we really start to see
the symptoms once it's just

00:55:59.980 --> 00:56:03.410
so widespread as
to be catastrophic.

